<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="T4sV1.Views.Time4SportAppPrivacyPolicy"
             Title="Privacy Policy"
             Shell.NavBarIsVisible="False">


    <ScrollView>
        <ScrollView.Background>
            <LinearGradientBrush EndPoint="0,1">
                <GradientStop Color="#e9fdb6" Offset="0.1" />
                <GradientStop Color="#9dc052" Offset="1.0" />
            </LinearGradientBrush>
        </ScrollView.Background>

        <VerticalStackLayout
            MaximumWidthRequest="420"
            Spacing="20"
            Padding="30,50">

            <!-- App Logo -->
            <Image
                Source="logo.png"
                HeightRequest="140"
                Margin="20"
                HorizontalOptions="Center" />

            <!-- Privacy Content -->
            <Label
                TextColor="Black"
                FontSize="14"
                LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                Text="
Time4Sport / Time4Wellbeing – Privacy and Data Protection Policy

We are committed to protecting your privacy and complying with the UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018.

This policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect personal data when you use the Time4Sport and Time4Wellbeing mobile and web applications.

────────────────────────────
What Data Do We Collect?

We may collect and store the following information:

• Parent / Guardian details – Name, email address, phone number  
• Child details – Name, date of birth, age, school (if applicable)  
• Health and wellbeing data – Height, weight, activity scores, wellbeing questionnaires  
• App usage data – Logins, feature usage, progress tracking  
• Communication data – Notifications and messages sent via the app  

All data relating to children is handled with the highest level of care and confidentiality.

────────────────────────────
How Is Your Data Used?

Your data is used solely to:

• Support children’s health, wellbeing, and physical activity tracking  
• Provide personalised insights, goals, and progress reports  
• Enable communication between parents, schools, and health professionals (where applicable)  
• Improve the functionality and effectiveness of our services  

We never sell personal data and do not share it with third parties unless legally required or explicitly agreed.

────────────────────────────
How Is Data Stored?

All data is securely stored using:

• Encrypted databases  
• Secure cloud infrastructure hosted within the UK / EU  
• SSL-protected connections  

Access is strictly limited to authorised personnel who require it to deliver the service.

────────────────────────────
How Long Is Data Retained?

Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary to deliver our services.
If an account becomes inactive or is closed, data will be securely deleted in line with our retention policy.

────────────────────────────
Your Rights

You have the right to:

• Request access to your data  
• Request correction of inaccurate data  
• Request deletion of your data  
• Withdraw consent at any time  

To exercise these rights, please contact us.

────────────────────────────
Contact Us

Email: support@time4wellbeinguk.com  
Phone: 01782 409677  

Data Protection Officer  
Time4Sport UK Ltd
" />

            <!-- Back Button -->
            <Button
                Text="Back"
                TextColor="White"
                BackgroundColor="#6b8e23"
                CornerRadius="12"
                HeightRequest="45"
                Clicked="Back_Clicked" />

        </VerticalStackLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</ContentPage>
